Dear Peter and all,

In my last message, I wrote that the forgetful functor DCat ---> Cat=20
is wrong because it is not a right Quillen functor.=20
The argument is not good enough.

I believe that a forgetful functor XStruc--->Cat should reflect=20
weak equivalences in addition to preserving them. =20

The forgetful functor DCat ---> Cat preserves weak equivalences
but it does not reflect them.=20
Because two objects in a dagger category can be isomorphic
without been unitary isomorphic.

Best,
aj

